summary: Pokemon Card of the Day Schedule: Noble Victories
title: Pokemon Card of the Day Schedule: Noble Victories
body:
Noble Victories was the final set before the arrival of Pokemon-EX, but it still managed to have an impact without having any. Victini and Vanilluxe helped form a rather good lock deck, for example. Terrakion became a top-tier threat in its own right, helped a lot by the fact that multiple top Pokemon of the time fell to strong Fighting-type attacks. Eelektrik became an incredible source of Lightning Energy acceleration, while Kyurem was a solid Water-type attacker. Durant brought back forcing the opponent to run out of cards as a viable strategy in one of the most annoying decks out there as well! And let’s not forget about Eviolite, great for those Pokemon-EX that soon appeared, as well as a disruptive Supporter in the form of N. This was a really impressive set with a ton of good cards, some of which stayed near the top even while power creep kept ramping up.
